{"id":"court","term":"Court","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>The enclosure of the tabernacle (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 27:9\">Ex. 27:9-19</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 40:8\">40:8</a>), of the temple (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 6:36\">1 Kings 6:36</a>), of a prison (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 3:25\">Neh. 3:25</a>), of a private house (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Samuel 17:18\">2 Sam. 17:18</a>), and of a king’s palace (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 20:4\">2 Kings 20:4</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Exodus 27:9","Exodus 40:8","1 Kings 6:36","Nehemiah 3:25","2 Samuel 17:18","2 Kings 20:4"]}